==German==
===Etymology===
{{OHG.}} ''haben'', {{OS.}} ''[[hebbian]]'', from Germanic ''*hab-æ-'' "have", related to {{L.}} ''[[capere]]'' "to [[grip]]", and {{L.}} ''[[habere]]'' "to have".

===Verb===
'''haben'''

# to [[have]]

==== Singular ====
* ich '''[[habe]]''' ''i have''
* du '''[[hast]]''' ''you have''
* er, sie, es '''[[hat]]''' '' he, she, it has''
==== Plural ====
* wir, sie '''[[haben]]''' ''we, they have''
* ihr '''[[habt]]''' ''you have''
==== Perfect ====
* '''[[gehabt]]'''

